after setting up the ssh connection
just clone your repo ctrl+shift +p using the ssh link

it will ask for the name and the email

if the ssh link will not clone anything proceed using the https link
then you will have to fix the https problem followin the instructions in the other file

REMEMBER! You can now use the new 'gh' commands by Github
With them you can link easily your account (but first need to setup the ssh connection)
and the clone your repos

Atom will not be able to read them automatically and put them in the Projects tab
You have to open the new repos and then drag them to you current working windows
(inside the Project tab)
